Nine people were killed and seven others injured in a head-on collision between a minibus and a taxi in the Eastern Cape on Friday morning, Arrive Alive, the South African road safety campaign, said. According to the Arrive Alive website five people were burnt beyond recognition in the crash that happened on the road between Zastron in the Free State and Sterkspruit in the Eastern Cape. The fire was extinguished while patients were treated by paramedics before the injured were transported to hospitals in the area. African News Agency For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.